 1255 , a legend responsible for several outbursts of anti-Semitism at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Hugh Plowfield was born about 1335, in Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Hugh Plowfield, was 26 and his mother, Unknown Plowfield, was 21. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1335–":"umbes 1335–Surnud","1335–Male":"1335–Surnud","1362–Female":"1362–Surnud","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1310":"1310","about 1335":"umbes 1335","1362":"1362","Evesham, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1335–":"noin 1335–Kuollut","1335–Male":"1335–Kuollut","1362–Female":"1362–Kuollut","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1315–Female":"1315–Kuollut","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1310":"1310","about 1335":"noin 1335","1362":"1362","Evesham, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1335–":"environ 1335–Décédé","1335–Male":"1335–Décédé","1362–Female":"1362–Décédée","1310–Male":"1310–Décédé","1315–Female":"1315–Décédée","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1310":"1310","about 1335":"environ 1335","1362":"1362","Evesham, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Hugh Plowfield est né environ 1335, à Gloucestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Hugh Plowfield, avait 26 ans et sa mère, Unknown Plowfield, avait 21 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"about 1335–":"um 1335–Verstorben","1335–Male":"1335–Verstorben","1362–Female":"1362–Verstorben","1310–Male":"1310–Verstorben","1315–Female